<TITLE> NSI officer arrested in 10-truck arms case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)The Criminal Investigation Department has shown a NSI field officer arrested in the sensational Chittagong '10-truck arms' haul case. Akbar Hossain was shown arrested on Sunday morning after a day-long interrogation at the CID office in the port city, Mohammad Muslim, special police superintendent of CID Chittagong zone, told bdnews24.com Akbar was produced before Chittagong metropolitan magistrate Abu Hannan with a five-day remand prayer. Assistant commissioner (prosecution) of Chittagong Metropolitan Police, MD Farid, told bdnews24.com that the judge granted two days for further interrogation. Akbar was serving as field officer for National Security Intelligence during the offloading of ten trucks of arms from a vessel at the restricted CUFL (Chittagong Urea Fertiliser Limited) jetty on the night of April 1, 2004, said investigators. Investigation officer Moniruzzaman, also assistant commissioner of CID police, told bdnews24.com that Akbar was shown arrested based on crucial information obtained during his day-long grilling on Saturday. Truck owners Taslim Mallick and Habibur Rahman during questioning had also previously informed CID officials that Akbar had rented the trucks for transport of the arms, said the IO. Meantime, CID also questioned nine more navy officers on Sunday, whom had been deputed to the Chittagong coast guard in 2004, bringing the total number of serving and former navy officers grilled in connection with the case over the past week to 29. bdnew
